original: Muhi, Carl-Gustaf Fredrik, kyrkoherde, Väröibacka, f. 1/10/06 i Gbg av kommin. Fredrik M. o. Hedvig Enig-stiedt. G. 33 m. Ingrid Jungquis-t. Barn: Gertrud f. 33, Carl-Eric 36, Birgitta 39, Ingvar 42, Ragnar 45. — Stud:ex. i Gbg 25, teo’1. fik ex. 26, teol. kand. i Lund 29, prakt. teol. prov »s. å., prästv. i Gbg 30. Past:adj. li Segtora 30, i Valinge 31-33, kommin. i Holsdjunga 33-47, k3Tkoh. i Värö sed. 47. I Hols-Ijunga ordf. i kyrkostämma, sko’lstyr., I Kl r na v : n d, il e d. av ko mm : f U’Hm., or df. i Röda kors-krets, sekr. i Kinds-Alarkskrets. av ASP.
translated: Muhi, Carl-Gustaf Fredrik, clergyman, Väröibacka, b. 1/10/06 in Gothenburg, son of curate Fredrik M. and Hedvig Enig-stiedt. Married in 1933 to Ingrid Jungquist. Children: Gertrud b. 1933, Carl-Eric b. 1936, Birgitta b. 1939, Ingvar b. 1942, Ragnar b. 1945. — Completed studies: graduated from high school in Gothenburg in 1925, theological examination in 1926, bachelor's degree in theology in Lund in 1929, practical theological examination in the same year, ordained as priest in Gothenburg in 1930. Served as assistant pastor in Segtora from 1930, in Valinge from 1931-1933, curate in Holsdjunga from 1933-1947, and vicar in Värö since 1947. In Holsdjunga served as chairman of the church council, school board, member of Klarna board, deputy of the curate's office, chairman of the Red Cross district, secretary of the Kinds-Alark district of the ASP (Association of Scientific Workers, Social Democrats).
